added.title: The Allergy
added.description: Gumball needs to find a cure for Darwin's allergy before he sneezes Elmore off the map. Darwin starts sneezing repeatedly and it seems he can't stop. The Wattersons figure maybe he's allergic to something. After a few guesses, they come to the conclusion that he is allergic to stupidity. Being surrounded by stupid people, this is something of a problem. And they need to find a solution before Darwin's increasingly explosive sneezes destroy the town.

added.title: The Mothers
added.description: It's Mother's Day and kids put their moms through a series of tests to determine who has the World's Greatest Mom.  It's Mother's Day, and Gumball and Darwin discover that Tobias and Banana Joe have both made a card for "The Best Mom in the World". Clearly Nicole Watterson is the Best Mom, but Tobias and BJ just won't admit it... So they organise a mom-off at the mall between Nicole, Banana Barbara and Jackie Wilson. Needless to say it gets pretty intense.

added.title: The Password
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are shocked to discover that Anais is Dad's favourite child. Mom has forced Dad to install a password on the computer. The pop-up clue advises them that the password is the name of Dad's favorite child. After trying "Gumball" and "Darwin" unsuccessfully, they discover the answer is, in fact, "Anais". They are determined to become Dad's favorites by any means necessary, even if it means undermining each other, plotting against Anais or driving a wedge between mom and dad . . .

added.title: The Procrastinators
added.description: Gumball and Darwin go to extraordinary lengths to avoid taking out the trash. Gumball and Darwin are offended when Mom calls them "procrastinators", once she's told them what it means. They promise to take the trash out by the time she gets home. As the clock slowly counts down, they discover that they will go to extraordinary lengths, no matter how inane, to avoid the task in hand.

added.title: The Shell
added.description: Gumball inadvertently cracks open Penny's shell and discovers who she really is inside . . . While performing a school play, Gumball is so nervous about kissing Penny that he accidentally headbutts her and cracks open her shell. They discover that under Penny's shell is an emotional shape-shifting inner self. Penny's father is determined for Penny to keep it hidden but Gumball encourages her to show the world who, or what, she really is . . .

added.title: The Cheese Stands Alone
added.description: The group takes a break from their search for the Heart of the Forest.

added.title: The Team Up
added.description: Craig turns to an unlikely ally in his time of need.

added.title: Camper on the Run
added.description: A runaway from a summer camp ends up at the Stump, but Craig suspects her story may not be what it seems.

added.title: Stink Bomb
added.description: An accidental stink bomb explosion causes the kids to evacuate the Creek, but Craig takes it upon himself to rescue those left behind in the stench.

added.title: The Evolution of Craig
added.description: Craig rescues a tadpole and decides to raise him into a level 100 frog!

added.title: Heatwave
added.description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: After learning that Burger has a trampoline, Apple and Onion pay him a visit. Burger thinks they came especially to see him and is overjoyed.

added.title: Baby Boi TP
added.description: Apple and Onion run out of toilet paper because Apple's been building a huge modern art sculpture with it. They're going to need more if Apple is to finish and Onion is to be able to resume his normal toilet activities.

added.title: Not Funny
added.description: With their 6 month friend anniversary approaching, Apple is in danger of losing his best friend.

added.title: Bun Bun
added.description: Finn brings a special delivery for Cinnamon Bun to the Fire Kingdom but it may come with a dangerous cost.

added.title: Normal Man
added.description: Stripped of his magic powers, Normal Man enlists Finn and Jake's help to rescue his brother Glob.

added.title: Elemental
added.description: Ice King discovers something buried deep beneath the Ice Kingdom that could change Ooo forever.

added.title: Five Short Tables
added.description: Fionna and Cake go on a cooking adventure to push Cake's art to an all-new level.

added.title: The Music Hole
added.description: While judging the hugest Battle of the Bands in the history of Ooo, Finn hears a mysterious new song.

added.title: Birthday Blowout
added.description: Puppycorn's birthday wish is stolen by Master Frown, the biggest downer in the kingdom! To recover it, Unikitty and Puppycorn will have to venture into the most depressing land ever, Frown Town! Will they manage to recover the birthday wish from Frown before his wish (and all wishes) are wished away forever?

added.title: Lab Cat
added.description: Dr. Fox's robot helpers go on strike, so Unikitty and Puppycorn volunteer to be her lab rats, er, research assistants in a bold new experiment rocketing them into space! But as the mission grows more dangerous, Dr. Fox is forced to choose between the scientific breakthrough of her dreams and ever seeing her friends again!

added.title: The Zone
added.description: Unikitty keeps losing at video games to her little brother Puppycorn, so she acquires a super-powered video game controller from Dr. Fox to help. To her surprise, it actually controls other people, and the castle goes into lockdown like a real-world video game! At first it seems fun, but will she learn that life isn't a game?

added.title: Too Many Unikittys
added.description: Unikitty comes to the conclusion that everyone would be a lot happier if they would just think the way she does, and with Dr. Fox's help, maybe they can! Unikitty copies her brainwaves into all her friends and turns them Unikitty-fied, so everyone can always be positive! But soon Unikitty quickly realizes there can be too much of a good Princess!

added.title: Film Fest
added.description: It's opening night at the Unikingdom Film Festival! Everyone's excited to see what the friends made, particularly Richard, who considers himself the ultimate film expert and can't wait to blow everyone else's films out of the water with his own. But after playing the critic, will Rick's film be a masterpiece or a flop?

added.title: In the Doghouse
added.description: Buttercup must go it alone to save her family from a kidnapping.

added.title: Salamander
added.description: When the professor is kidnapped, the girls must go to a mysterious island to save him.

added.title: Witch's Crew
added.description: On Halloween Night, Morbucks summons a monster that she didn't expect.

added.title: Checkin' Out!
added.description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

added.title: Drama Bomb
added.description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

added.title: Dog Hotel
added.description: With no place to stay while their cave gets fumigated, the Bears book a night at a hotel for dogs.

added.title: Bear Lift
added.description: To help raise money to save Darrell's store, the Bears use the stack as a taxi through a ride share app.

added.title: The Nom Nom Show
added.description: Things go awry while Nom Nom shoots his first television show. The Bears offer to help and appear on the show.

added.title: Ice Cave
added.description: Ralph takes over the cave and turns it into a snowy fortress where he reigns as king over the Bears and Charlie.

added.title: Spa Day
added.description: The Bears have a relaxing day at the spa. Grizz tries to get everything the spa has to offer. Panda gets trapped in the steam room with an old man. And Ice Bear plays ping pong.

added.title: Rock Show
added.description: Chad's band Dogmon, plays a show for the first time in years, giving Clarence and Mary a chance to really rock out.

added.title: Pool's Out for Summer
added.description: The boys go to the Aberdale Community Pool for a day of wet fun! While Jeff slowly wades in the shallow end, getting used to the water, Sumo tries to conquer the diving board, redeeming himself from last summer's bellyflop, and Clarence sneaks past the lifeguards into the hot tub for a boiling surprise.

added.title: The Big Game
added.description: Chad takes Clarence to his first big game! Clarence takes it all in - the crack of the bat, the touchdown dances, the slam-dunks and of course, hotdogs and popcorn! But will Clarence get to fulfill his dream of meeting Aberdale's beloved mascot?

added.title: The Boxcurse Children
added.description: Clarence, Jeff, and Sumo stumble upon a mysterious box. After they open it, some strange things begin to happen. Convinced they've unlocked a curse, they become determined to reverse it!

added.title: Karate Mom
added.description: After surprising Clarence with Martial Arts classes at the "Aberdojo," Mary gets talked into joining the class herself. She loves the slow-paced lessons in discipline and control, but Clarence just wants to have fun and kick butt! Can Mary convince Clarence to stick with the class, earn his belt and have some fun with her?

added.title: Mystery Noise
added.description: It's Sleepover Dream Night in the RV and the gang just wants to get some sleep to dream their dreams, but when a mysterious noise keeps them awake, their grip on sanity begins slipping.

added.title: Charlie Burgers
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and crew help a friendly dog, Charlie Burgers, find his lost ball by literally turning the world upside down.

added.title: Shorts
added.description: A collection of shorts where Uncle Grandpa and the gang host a news program that goes awry, two turtles decide whether things are cool or dumb, and Uncle Grandpa goes on an accidental rampage trying to hit a pinata.

added.title: Perfect Kid
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid become perfect by turning him into a robot.  But when the robot tries to destroy him for being imperfect, Uncle Grandpa goes on the run.

added.title: Big in Japan
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and the gang help a kid make a giant monster movie, they cast Mr. Gus as the monster.  But things get tense on the set when Mr. Gus wants to flex his acting muscles while Uncle Grandpa only wants him to flex his monster muscles.

removed.title: Putting Together The Pieces
removed.description: The journey begins to the Heart of the Forest.

removed.title: Heart of the Forest Finale
removed.description: The epic finale of the quest for the Heart of the Forest.
